>> Non-anonymous FTP account required; see GETTING_ACCESS.

>I'm sorry, but I don't follow you here: is "GETTING_ACCESS" a section in
>the FAQ?  If so, we seem to be between FAQs here: the old one has
>(apparently) expired and a new one hasn't been posted yet.  Can you
>possibly give me details on how I can get hold of the paper you mention?

GETTING_ACCESS is a file in one of the directories of ripem.msu.edu. I
think it is /pub. It is available via anom ftp and gives details of how
to get access to other files. Basically, it requires email back to the
ripem ftp site validating you are accessing from the US and will abide
by US crypto export rules.
